    • adjusted

      public boolean adjusted()
      Finds the row and column of upper left corner of enemy and bottom right corner. If the rows and columns are different then enemy is not centered on tile.
      Returns:
      Whether enemy is located in center of tile.

    • lineOfSight

      public boolean lineOfSight()
      Finds if tow parallel lines with lineOfSight, both being half of enemy width distant from line of sight, do not pass trough tile which enemy can not move onto. Line of sight is line between enemy and player coordinates.
      Returns:
      whether an enemy can see a player.

    • findPlayer

      public int findPlayer​(int row, int column, int level)
      Searches for player row and column on map using breadth first algorithm, tracing trough tiles an enemy can visit.
      Parameters:
      row - starting row on map.
      column - starting column on map.
      level - starting level of breadth search.
      Returns:
      level of the first map tile satisfying search condition or max level if tile wan not found.
